age or environment property is indicated. Prefer runtime tests around zio.prelude.Assertion helpers, and only attempt macro-specific coverage by compiling a small Scala 2.13 snippet rather than calling macro internals directly.\",\n./stats/org.apache.maven.scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/1.11.1/execution-metrics.json:77:      \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n./stats/org.apache.maven.scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/1.11.1/execution-metrics.json:78:      \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n./stats/org.apache.maven.scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/2.0.0/execution-metrics.json:77:      \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n./stats/org.apache.maven.scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/2.0.0/execution-metrics.json:78:      \"agent_guidance\": \"For 2.0.0 tests, avoid org.apache.maven.scm.log.DefaultLog because the legacy Maven SCM logging API was removed in favor of SLF4J-backed consumers. Use the 2.0.0 constructors, such as GitStatusConsumer(File), GitRemoteInfoConsumer(String), and an instance of GitRemoteInfoCommand with an environment map before calling createCommandLine. Meaningful coverage can be built with command-line construction and consumer parsing without adding dependencies or external services.\",\n./stats/org.apache.maven.scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/2.1.0/execution-metrics.json:77:      \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n./stats/org.apache.maven.scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/2.1.0/execution-metrics.json:78:      \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n./stats/org.apache.maven.scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/1.10.0/execution-metrics.json:77:      \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n./stats/org.apache.maven.scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/1.10.0/execution-metrics.json:78:      \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n./stats/dev.zio/zio-streams_2.13/2.0.22/execution-metrics.json:53:      \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n./stats/dev.zio/zio-streams_2.13/2.0.22/execution-metrics.json:54:      \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. Tests should use the normal Scala scaffold and run ZIO stream ef